	  <h2>CROSS-CHAIN RECOVERY POLICY</h2>
	  <p>Recovery of cross-chain deposits is a very dangerous and time-consuming process. Not all deposits may be recovered, and the level of complexity, risk and time frames depends both on the type of currency and the used address for the deposit.<p>
	  <p>Having taken into consideration all the factors, the GlobeEx team has developed the following fee structure of a cross-chain deposit recovery:</p>
	  <p>GlobeEx will recover only those cross-chain deposits that exceed 250.00 USD at the moment of transaction within a 30 day banking period. The User has to pay 10% fee (minimum 100.00 USD, maximum 500.00 USD) towards the services for the recovery. In order to enable the recovery process, the User has to replenish his/her account with above mentioned amount. After the successful replenishment, the GlobeEx support and finance departments shall take steps required for the deposit recovery. The fee will be written off from the User’s account in case of the successful transaction.</p>
	  <p>The Users should remember about the described difficulties of the cross-chain recovery process and take into consideration a significant number of deposits mistakenly sent to the wrong address. The GlobeEx team dedicates its best efforts to resolve the issue within the shortest time frames. Thus, GlobeEx recommends you to be patient during the process of cross chain recovery.</p>

	  <p>Attention: GlobeEx will not recover coins and tokens which are not listed and supported by the GlobeEx platform.</p>
